<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="xl-section xl-faq-section">
    <div class="xl-container xl-faq-container">
        <div class="xl-section-header">
            <div class="xl-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
            <h2>Common questions.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="xl-faq-grid">
            <details class="xl-faq-item">
                <summary>Does the AI Formula Copilot work for Google Sheets too?</summary>
                <p>Yes — formulas are generated for both Excel and Google Sheets. The syntax is nearly identical for most functions, and the AI notes any differences when they matter.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="xl-faq-item">
                <summary>Is my data stored after I upload it?</summary>
                <p>No. Uploaded files are processed in memory and never written to permanent storage. We don't store, share, or train on your spreadsheet data.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="xl-faq-item">
                <summary>What's the difference between ExcelToolStack and PdfToolStack?</summary>
                <p>ExcelToolStack handles spreadsheet workflows — formulas, data cleaning, CSV conversion. PdfToolStack handles document workflows — compress, merge, sign, extract invoice data, review contracts. They share the same account and are available together in the Bundle plan.</p>
            </details>
            <details class="xl-faq-item">
                <summary>Do I need an account to use the tools?</summary>
                <p>Free tools work without any account. AI tools and batch processing require a Pro account. Signing up takes under a minute via Google, GitHub, or email.</p>
            </details>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- FOOTER CTA -->
<section class="xl-footer-cta">
    <div class="xl-container">
        <h2>Ready to work faster in Excel?</h2>
        <p>Start with the AI Formula Copilot — free, no signup required.</p>
        <a href="/ai-excel-formula-generator" class="xl-btn-primary xl-btn-large">
            Try AI Formula Copilot Free →
        </a>
    </div>
</section>
